<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 4:32PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Sherman
County through 500 PM CDT...
At 432 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
capable of producing a landspout over Stratford, moving east at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph, and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured
objects.
Locations impacted include...
Stratford and Texhoma.
LANDSPOUT...POSSIBLE
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
